<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Notted - Delete Account</title>

  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background: #f7f8fc;
      color: #222;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 40px 20px;
    }

    .card {
      background: #fff;
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 30px;
      box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
    }

    h1 {
      color: #19026c;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    h2 {
      margin-top: 30px;
      color: #19026c;
    }

    ol, ul {
      padding-left: 22px;
    }

    .note {
      background: #f0edff;
      border-left: 4px solid #19026c;
      padding: 14px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    footer {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 30px;
      color: #777;
      font-size: 14px;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="card">
      <h1>Delete Your Account – Notted</h1>

      <p>
        This page explains how users can request deletion of their Notted account
        and the data associated with it.
      </p>

      <h2>How to Delete Your Account</h2>

      <ol>
        <li>Open the Notted app.</li>
        <li>Go to the Profile page.</li>
        <li>Tap Delete Account.</li>
        <li>Confirm the deletion request.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Data That Will Be Deleted</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>User profile information</li>
        <li>Personal tasks</li>
        <li>Board notes</li>
        <li>Goals and schedule data</li>
        <li>Media attached to tasks, if applicable</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>

      <p>
        Once the account deletion is confirmed, the associated data will be
        permanently deleted. Some limited information may be retained only if
        required by law, security, or fraud prevention obligations.
      </p>

      <h2>Need Help?</h2>

      <p>
        If you cannot access the app or need help deleting your account, please
        contact us by email:
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>support@pleroxy.co</strong>
      </p>

      <div class="note">
        Please include the email address used for your Notted account when
        contacting support.
      </div>
    </div>

    <footer>
      © 2026 Notted. All rights reserved.
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
